result.execSummary:
NATHANIEL L HAMEED was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means NATHANIEL L HAMEED was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

1:22 PM Prosecuting attorney Gregory A. Parker in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant NATHANIEL L HAMEED in court, in custody.  Attorney John Miller Carroll appeared by video for NATHANIEL L HAMEED.  Judge reads the extradition paperwork to the defendant word for word for the court on record.  
Judge watches the defendant sign his paperwork.  Judge signs the paperwork.  
Mr Hameed does disagree with the statement that he resisted or obstructed. Defendant made a note of this on the paperwork. Judge and attorneys don't believe that statement has any relevance for this extradition waiver.

8:22 am Prosecuting attorney Laura Nelson in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant NATHANIEL L HAMEED appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney John Miller Carroll in court for NATHANIEL L HAMEED.   Defendant asks Atty to withdraw from case.  Does not need or want an attorney for this case.  Not contesting extradition any longer.  
State believes Florida is working on transportation arrangements but doesn't have a time frame today.  
Reschedule this for 1pm today so extradition waiver paperwork can be prepared and defendant can be brought over in person at 1pm
